# Dependency Rules

All NestJS packages must use the same major version.

For NestJS 11:

@nestjs/common 11.x
@nestjs/core 11.x
@nestjs/platform-express 11.x
@nestjs/config 4.x or later

Never mix NestJS 11 with packages built for NestJS 10 or lower.


# Database Connection Rules

The application uses MySQL as the primary database.

Database connections must use environment variables stored in a `.env` file.

Never hardcode credentials in source code.

Use the following format:

DATABASE_URL="mysql://USERNAME:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DATABASE"

Example:

DATABASE_URL="mysql://root:password@localhost:3306/openlibrary"

Prisma must read the connection from:

env("DATABASE_URL")



# Angular Dependency Rules

When generating Angular projects:

Angular 20 must use compatible dependencies.

Required versions:

typescript >=5.8 <6.0
@angular/* 20.x
@angular-devkit/build-angular 20.x

Never install TypeScript versions lower than 5.8 when using Angular 20.

Always verify dependency compatibility before generating package.json.
